For about the last two decades, Babcock–Leighton type flux transport dynamo models have been extensively used to explain the variabilities in the solar cycle. The first landmark paper in this series came from Charbonneau and Dikpati (2000) who included stochastic fluctuations in their 2D (axisymmetric) flux transport dynamo model. For this, they added a stochastic term with a coherence time of a month in the α\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
